				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$99 \%$$\end{document} confidence). In other words, a model’s own confidence score cannot be trusted. To overcome this problem, we use a set of labeled experimentally known compounds as side information to help determine a model’s trustworthiness for a particular unseen test example. The trust score is defined as follows:1T(Xi)=1−dXi,{Xj}j∈cidXi,{Xj}j∈ci+dXi,{Xj}j∉ci.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
